.TH RASTER-IMPRESS 1 "2025-12-03" "Raster Impress CLI by Matthias W."
.SH NAME
raster-impress \- CLI tool for raster analysis and feature extraction
.SH SYNOPSIS
raster-impress [file] [--stats] [--histogram [output.tif]] [--ndvi [output.tif]] [--slope [output.tif]] [--hillshade [output.tif]] [--relief [output_prefix]] [--metadata] [--quality] [--extract DSM DGM] [--output OUTPUT] [--silent] [--version]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Raster Impress CLI analyzes raster data (GeoTIFF, NetCDF, HDF5). Computes statistics, histogram, NDVI, slope, hillshade, relief, metadata, quality check, and extracts features (vegetation, impervious surfaces, buildings) from DSM and DGM rasters.

All output files are generated automatically if no output filename is provided; default filenames are derived from the input raster (e.g., raster_slope.tif, raster_ndvi.tif, impervious_surfaces.shp).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-stats
Compute basic raster statistics (min, max, mean, stddev).
.TP
\-\-histogram [output.tif]
Compute histogram of raster values. Optional output filename; default adds '_hist.tif' to input raster. Also generates a PNG plot.
.TP
\-\-ndvi [output.tif]
Compute NDVI (requires at least 2 bands). Optional output filename; default adds '_ndvi.tif' to input raster. Also generates a PNG plot.
.TP
\-\-slope [output.tif]
Compute Slope (DEM required). Optional output filename; default adds '_slope.tif' to input raster. Also generates a PNG plot.
.TP
\-\-hillshade [output.tif]
Compute Hillshade (DEM required). Optional output filename; default adds '_hillshade.tif' to input raster. Also generates a PNG plot.
.TP
\-\-relief [output_prefix]
Compute color relief with hillshade overlay (DEM required). Optional output filename prefix; default adds '_relief' to input raster.
.TP
\-\-metadata
Show raster metadata (width, height, bands, CRS, transform, nodata values).
.TP
\-\-quality
Perform quality check on raster bands (NoData pixels, shape consistency).
.TP
\-\-extract DSM DGM
Perform feature extraction using DSM and DGM rasters. Generates pixel-accurate shapefiles for vegetation, impervious surfaces, and buildings.
.TP
\-\-output OUTPUT
Specify output folder for results (default: current directory).
.TP
\-\-silent
Suppress log output.
.TP
\-\-version
Show CLI version.
.SH EXAMPLES
Compute slope, NDVI, and histogram with default output filenames:
.nf
raster-impress raster.tif --slope --ndvi --histogram
.fi

Compute slope and NDVI with custom output filenames:
.nf
raster-impress raster.tif --slope output/myslope.tif --ndvi output/myndvi.tif
.fi

Compute relief with default output prefix:
.nf
raster-impress raster.tif --relief
.fi

Compute relief with custom output prefix:
.nf
raster-impress raster.tif --relief output/myrelief
.fi

Perform feature extraction using DSM and DGM:
.nf
raster-impress raster.tif --extract dsm.tif dgm.tif --output output_folder
.fi
